claim.claim-text:
1. A method of controlling the application of power during faults conditions comprising:
generating a power signal to deliver to a power sink, the power signal having a programmable waveform;
monitoring a parameter to determine whether the parameter is within a range of parameter values associated with operation of the power sink;
comparing the parameter against one or more fault profiles;
detecting a fault as a function of a value for the parameter being noncompliant;
classifying the fault as being associated with a first subset of faults if the parameter matches a first portion of a fault profile of the one or more fault profiles;
classifying the fault as being associated with a second subset of faults if the parameter matches a second portion of the fault profile; and
initiating a fault action.

11. A non-transitory computer-readable storaqe medium configured to determine faults during application of power, the computer-readable medium comprising executable instructions configured to:
cause generation of a power signal to deliver to a power sink, the power signal having a programmable waveform;
monitor a parameter to determine whether the parameter is within a range of parameter values associated with operation of the power sink;
compare the parameter against one or more fault profiles;
detect a fault as a function of a value for the parameter being noncompliant;
classify the fault as being associated with a first subset of faults if the parameter matches a first portion of a fault profile of the one or more fault profiles;
classify the fault as being associated with a second subset of faults if the parameter matches a second portion of the fault profile; and
cause initiation of a fault action.

16. An apparatus comprising:
an input terminal configured to receive data from one or more sensors with which to determine a parameter;
a memory including executable instructions; and
a processor configured to execute the executable instructions to:
monitor the parameter to determine whether the parameter is within a range of parameter values associated with operation of a power sink;
compare the parameter against one or more fault profiles;
detect a fault as a function of a value for the parameter being noncompliant;
classify the fault as being associated with a first type of fault if the parameter matches a first portion of a fault profile of the one or more fault profiles;
classify the fault as being associated with a second type of fault if the parameter matches a second portion of the fault profile;
cause initiation of a fault action; and
cause generation of a power signal to deliver to the power sink, the power signal having a programmable waveform.

18. The apparatus of claim 16 wherein the processor is further configured to:
identify the fault as a nascent fault;
increase a degree of maturity for the nascent fault while the value for the parameter is associated with a first subset of parameter values;
decrease the degree of maturity for the nascent fault while the value for the parameter is associated with a second subset of parameter values; and
indicate that the nascent fault is a mature fault if the degree of maturity meets a threshold degree of maturity.
